{"model":"claude-3-7-sonnet-20250219","id":"msg_bdrk_01NRbNe76fwoBiXobXc59xnP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"To multiply 17 * 23, I'll break it down step by step.\n\nMethod 1: Traditional multiplication\n   17\nx  23\n-----\n   51  (3 * 17)\n  340  (20 * 17)\n-----\n  391  (sum)\n\nMethod 2: Alternative approach\nI can also think of this as:\n17 * 23 = 17 * (20 + 3) = 17 * 20 + 17 * 3 = 340 + 51 = 391\n\nLet me double-check with another method:\nMethod 3: \n17 * 23 = (10 + 7) * 23 = 10 * 23 + 7 * 23 = 230 + 161 = 391\n\nSo the answer is 391.","signature":"ErcBCkgICxABGAIiQAqvBGINTXXe+JUMyaN0crXrJE/2l/c3F5MwXP0gjkVnpJ1QWVY5j5gtaMQyChexUVVLohneLKTFw1WA96/+O+QSDPU2Z47xKV/94IBq8RoMcJ6r7fHUIlJ6VEBYIjDAeFjg+sFPyNAjNLNTmQIkeHbMy06WYolPJsclB3b+YTZMX7+uMuYThVnJV7n1wnoqHdelie8r63mg2zTYElsIJTcYPZIRYNIY/GXbWhxpGAI="},{"type":"text","text":"# Calculating 17 × 23\n\nI'll solve this step by step using a couple of approaches.\n\n## Method 1: Standard vertical multiplication\n```\n   17\n×  23\n-----\n   51   (= 17 × 3)\n  340   (= 17 × 20)\n-----\n  391   (= 51 + 340)\n```\n\n## Method 2: Distributive property\nI can break this down by splitting 23:\n- 17 × 23 = 17 × (20 + 3)\n- = (17 × 20) + (17 × 3)\n- = 340 + 51\n- = 391\n\nTherefore, 17 × 23 = 391"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":54,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":382}}